OL,3,CWest of England Mayor hints at tourism
OL,4,Ctax for Bristol and Bath
OL,6,FEarlier this year, councillors in Bath
OL,7,Fvoted unanimously in favour of the
OL,8,Fprinciple of a so-called tourism tax,
OL,9,Farguing that a small contribution from
OL,10,Fvisitors would help keep the city
OL,11,F"clean and safe and welcoming".
OL,13,FBath has six million visitors a year
OL,14,Fand the council claims a "modest"
OL,15,Fcharge per night would raise a couple
OL,16,Fof million pounds annually to help
OL,17,Fstruggling council budgets.
